## Tables

### `households` — RLS ✅ enabled

The top-level entity. A household groups members together. Created by one authenticated user; others join via `invite_code`.

| Column | Type | Nullable | Default | Notes |
|--------|------|----------|---------|-------|
| `id` | uuid | NO | `gen_random_uuid()` | PK |
| `name` | text | NO | — | Display name of the household |
| `invite_code` | text | NO | `substr(md5(random()::text), 1, 8)` | Unique 8-char code used to invite members |
| `created_at` | timestamptz | NO | `now()` | — |
image_url text

**RLS policies:**
- `SELECT` — user must be a member (`household_members.user_id = auth.uid()`)
- `INSERT` — any authenticated user can create a household

---

### `household_members` — RLS ✅ enabled

Join table linking `auth.users` to `households`. Each row is one person's membership in one household.

| Column | Type | Nullable | Default | Notes |
|--------|------|----------|---------|-------|
| `id` | uuid | NO | `gen_random_uuid()` | PK |
| `household_id` | uuid | NO | — | FK → `households.id` |
| `user_id` | uuid | NO | — | FK → `auth.users.id` |
| `nickname` | text | YES | — | Optional display name within household |
| `is_rent_owner` | boolean | NO | `false` | Whether this member pays/collects rent |
| `joined_at` | timestamptz | NO | `now()` | — |

**RLS policies:**
- `SELECT` — user can view members of any household they belong to
- `INSERT` — any authenticated user can join a household

