## Relationship Map

```
auth.users
  └── household_members (user_id)
        └── households (household_id)
              ├── expense_categories (household_id)
              │     ├── category_splits (category_id) ←→ household_members
              │     └── expenses (category_id)
              │           └── expense_splits (expense_id) ←→ household_members
              ├── shopping_lists (household_id)
              │     └── shopping_list_items (shopping_list_id)
              ├── recipes (household_id)
              │     ├── recipe_ingredients (recipe_id)
              │     └── recipe_steps (recipe_id)
              └── household_items (household_id) ←→ expense_categories (default_category_id)

auth.users
  └── shopping_lists (user_id)  [when owner_type = 'user']
```

---

## Security Status

RLS is only enabled on `households` and `household_members`. The following 10 tables are **fully exposed** to the `anon` and `authenticated` roles — anyone with the anon key can read or modify every row:

`shopping_lists`, `shopping_list_items`, `recipes`, `recipe_ingredients`, `recipe_steps`, `expense_categories`, `category_splits`, `expenses`, `expense_splits`, `household_items`

Before shipping any feature that touches these tables, RLS must be enabled with appropriate policies.
